# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorPath3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Arriving in the throne room, Sarah could see that there was already a significant presence of Mythran soldiers."
    new "Arriving in the throne room, Sarah could see that there was already a significant presence of Mythran soldiers."

    old "Their army was larger than their mercenary company by many times, and still, it represented only a small part of the total Mythran army."
    new "Their army was larger than their mercenary company by many times, and still, it represented only a small part of the total Mythran army."

    old "Mythra truly was a superpower without equals."
    new "Mythra truly was a superpower without equals."

    old "It was fortunate then for the rest of the world that Mythra was so prone to infighting, or else every living soul would have to answer to them."
    new "It was fortunate then for the rest of the world that Mythra was so prone to infighting, or else every living soul would have to answer to them."

    old "Sarah marched slightly behind Vaelen, past the host of Mythran soldiers."
    new "Sarah marched slightly behind Vaelen, past the host of Mythran soldiers."

    old "Near the front, she saw that the Mythran prince was already waiting."
    new "Near the front, she saw that the Mythran prince was already waiting."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Shah Mahda! Come out of your little rat hiding hole before I send in my men to drag you out like the vermin you are."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Shah Mahda! Come out of your little rat hiding hole before I send in my men to drag you out like the vermin you are."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"If you're not going to live honorably, at least you can die honorably."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"If you're not going to live honorably, at least you can die honorably."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Whatever, I don't have the patience for this. Men! Tear down the barricade and drag these rats out, alive!"
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Whatever, I don't have the patience for this. Men! Tear down the barricade and drag these rats out, alive!"

    old "A sound cut through all the others, as the room went silent."
    new "A sound cut through all the others, as the room went silent."

    old "The clattering of wood, then steel."
    new "The clattering of wood, then steel."

    old "Piece by piece, the fragments that made up the barricade to the royal quarters came down, being taken apart from the inside."
    new "Piece by piece, the fragments that made up the barricade to the royal quarters came down, being taken apart from the inside."

    old "Climbing out through the small passage, was the Shah."
    new "Climbing out through the small passage, was the Shah."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Aah, finally. I was afraid my men would have to break a sweat getting you out of there."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Aah, finally. I was afraid my men would have to break a sweat getting you out of there."

    old "Sarah watched the Shah walk up towards them."
    new "Sarah watched the Shah walk up towards them."

    old "Despite having lost, he seemed entirely unaffected. He still walked with the confidence of kings, the kind that reminded her of her own father."
    new "Despite having lost, he seemed entirely unaffected. He still walked with the confidence of kings, the kind that reminded her of her own father."

    old "His imperial gaze slowly drifted across the room."
    new "His imperial gaze slowly drifted across the room."

    old "For a moment, his eyes settled on Sarah. She could feel herself pinned to the ground."
    new "For a moment, his eyes settled on Sarah. She could feel herself pinned to the ground."

    old "I see your mercenary lapdogs are here."
    new "I see your mercenary lapdogs are here."

    old "The Mythran prince laughed."
    new "The Mythran prince laughed."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Aah, it speaks. I was beginning to think you'd be too scared to even come out."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Aah, it speaks. I was beginning to think you'd be too scared to even come out."

    old "A worm like you won't make me cower."
    new "A worm like you won't make me cower."

    old "Sarah could see rage flash across the face of the Mythran prince."
    new "Sarah could see rage flash across the face of the Mythran prince."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"You killed my nephew. You brought all this upon yourself, remember that while you hear your family get tortured to death."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"You killed my nephew. You brought all this upon yourself, remember that while you hear your family get tortured to death."

    old "Sarah could see the Shah's face. It didn't move at all."
    new "Sarah could see the Shah's face. It didn't move at all."

    old "She leaned in to Vaelen and whispered to him."
    new "She leaned in to Vaelen and whispered to him."

    old "There's something wrong."
    new "There's something wrong."

    old "Why...why is he out here?"
    new "Why...why is he out here?"

    old "To surrender, what else?"
    new "To surrender, what else?"

    old "Does he look like someone that is about to surrender?"
    new "Does he look like someone that is about to surrender?"

    old "Vaelen didn't answer her."
    new "Vaelen didn't answer her."

    old "The Mythran prince moved closer towards the Shah."
    new "The Mythran prince moved closer towards the Shah."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Enough! You and the rest of your debased dynasty have been tolerated long enough."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Enough! You and the rest of your debased dynasty have been tolerated long enough."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Your allies have abandoned you. Your armies are shattered. Your city will soon be put to the sword. You've lost!"
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Your allies have abandoned you. Your armies are shattered. Your city will soon be put to the sword. You've lost!"

    old "Not all my allies have abandoned my house."
    new "Not all my allies have abandoned my house."

    old "A pause lingered in the room."
    new "A pause lingered in the room."

    old "Mythran Prince\" \"Soldiers! Seize him, strip him and whip him till he begs for mercy! Maybe that will bring some sense back to him."
    new "Mythran Prince\" \"Soldiers! Seize him, strip him and whip him till he begs for mercy! Maybe that will bring some sense back to him."

    old "Sarah watched as a small cadre of soldiers began to move forward."
    new "Sarah watched as a small cadre of soldiers began to move forward."

    old "Suddenly, they stopped."
    new "Suddenly, they stopped."

    old "Turning her eyes back towards the Shah, she saw an object emerge from his robes."
    new "Turning her eyes back towards the Shah, she saw an object emerge from his robes."

    old "A dagger. A handle as black as obsidian, a blade glowing in deep crimson red."
    new "A dagger. A handle as black as obsidian, a blade glowing in deep crimson red."

    old "She watched as the Shah raised his arm high above his head."
    new "She watched as the Shah raised his arm high above his head."

    old "The room had gone silent."
    new "The room had gone silent."

    old "Though none could say why, everyone could feel the item reverberate. A thing that commanded respect, awe."
    new "Though none could say why, everyone could feel the item reverberate. A thing that commanded respect, awe."

    old "My family hails back centuries. Millenia."
    new "My family hails back centuries. Millenia."

    old "My allies on this side have failed me, but my allies on the other side won't!"
    new "My allies on this side have failed me, but my allies on the other side won't!"

    old "With a single slash, Sarah watched the dagger cut through the air."
    new "With a single slash, Sarah watched the dagger cut through the air."

    old "At first, she believed it had been nothing. Perhaps a final gesture from a man truly gone insane."
    new "At first, she believed it had been nothing. Perhaps a final gesture from a man truly gone insane."

    old "But then she could see."
    new "But then she could see."

    old "Tracing the movement of the blade, Sarah could see the glimmer of a cut. A wound across the face of creation."
    new "Tracing the movement of the blade, Sarah could see the glimmer of a cut. A wound across the face of creation."

    old "Rapidly expanding, the wound grew and grew, and Sarah could now see into it. A void, deeper more devoid of light than any she had ever known."
    new "Rapidly expanding, the wound grew and grew, and Sarah could now see into it. A void, deeper more devoid of light than any she had ever known."

    old "Then two sets of claws emerged, seizing upon the wound and tearing it open entirely."
    new "Then two sets of claws emerged, seizing upon the wound and tearing it open entirely."

    old "Birthed from this violation of reality, a creature slithered out."
    new "Birthed from this violation of reality, a creature slithered out."

    old "It's body black as ink, it slithered and moved like a snake."
    new "It's body black as ink, it slithered and moved like a snake."

    old "It's brute claws pierced the stone of the old palace, and with great effort it pulled itself out from whatever dimension it called home, into Sarah's world."
    new "It's brute claws pierced the stone of the old palace, and with great effort it pulled itself out from whatever dimension it called home, into Sarah's world."

    old "The thing's face, as white as a mask made out of porcelain, its only feature its pitless eyes and razor teeth like those of a shark."
    new "The thing's face, as white as a mask made out of porcelain, its only feature its pitless eyes and razor teeth like those of a shark."

    old "Having looked on, first in stunned silence, a single soldier was the first to break their collective trauma."
    new "Having looked on, first in stunned silence, a single soldier was the first to break their collective trauma."

    old "A scream rang out. Then, a chorus of countless soldiers, screaming."
    new "A scream rang out. Then, a chorus of countless soldiers, screaming."

    old "Sarah watched as the beast suddenly leapt forward with a speed that belied its enormous size."
    new "Sarah watched as the beast suddenly leapt forward with a speed that belied its enormous size."

    old "The thing stood before the Mythran prince, who looked up at it."
    new "The thing stood before the Mythran prince, who looked up at it."

    old "So great was his fear of the thing, that even the idea of resisting his own death filled him with dread."
    new "So great was his fear of the thing, that even the idea of resisting his own death filled him with dread."

    old "The creature's snakelike body sat half upright. Even so, it towered over the Mythran prince by at least three times."
    new "The creature's snakelike body sat half upright. Even so, it towered over the Mythran prince by at least three times."

    old "Then it snapped."
    new "Then it snapped."

    old "The creature's mouth snapped around the Mythran prince's head, catching him across his shoulder and upper chest with its teeth."
    new "The creature's mouth snapped around the Mythran prince's head, catching him across his shoulder and upper chest with its teeth."

    old "In one fell gulp, Sarah watched the Mythran prince being swallowed, dissapearing into the creature's stomach."
    new "In one fell gulp, Sarah watched the Mythran prince being swallowed, dissapearing into the creature's stomach."

    old "If the prince had screamed, Sarah didn't hear it."
    new "If the prince had screamed, Sarah didn't hear it."

    old "The only sound she could hear for certain among the chaos and screams, was the laughing."
    new "The only sound she could hear for certain among the chaos and screams, was the laughing."

    old "The Shah, beyond himself, laughing hysterically at the carnage."
    new "The Shah, beyond himself, laughing hysterically at the carnage."

    old "We need to leave!"
    new "We need to leave!"

    old "Sarah gripped Vaelen by the shoulder."
    new "Sarah gripped Vaelen by the shoulder."

    old "She felt his body flinch, as if she had pulled him from somewhere very far away."
    new "She felt his body flinch, as if she had pulled him from somewhere very far away."

    old "Now! Or that thing is gonna kill us all!"
    new "Now! Or that thing is gonna kill us all!"

    old "Yes...yes! Run!"
    new "Yes...yes! Run!"

    old "Together, they began to run towards the only exit that the throne room had."
    new "Together, they began to run towards the only exit that the throne room had."

    old "As they ran, Sarah could feel the chaos in the room growing as soldiers all around them were wildly running, many dropping their weapons, falling, tumbling over one another."
    new "As they ran, Sarah could feel the chaos in the room growing as soldiers all around them were wildly running, many dropping their weapons, falling, tumbling over one another."

    old "A shade rushed by her."
    new "A shade rushed by her."

    old "Sarah saw the creature, it's limbs wildly flailing as it dragged its own snake body across the throne room."
    new "Sarah saw the creature, it's limbs wildly flailing as it dragged its own snake body across the throne room."

    old "It was fast. So fast."
    new "It was fast. So fast."

    old "Before she realized, the thing had placed itself between the door and the soldiers."
    new "Before she realized, the thing had placed itself between the door and the soldiers."

    old "An entire army trembled."
    new "An entire army trembled."

    old "Whatever the thing was, it possessed enough intelligence to block their escape."
    new "Whatever the thing was, it possessed enough intelligence to block their escape."

    old "Sarah watched the thing coil its body and snap foward."
    new "Sarah watched the thing coil its body and snap foward."

    old "A soldier, too far out from the others, caught in the things teeth."
    new "A soldier, too far out from the others, caught in the things teeth."

    old "He screamed as the creature ripped off and swallowed his arm, the blood pooling from his wound."
    new "He screamed as the creature ripped off and swallowed his arm, the blood pooling from his wound."

    old "The soldier had worn armor, perhaps even better than the kind anyone in her mercenary company had, and the creature had sliced through it like it was nothing."
    new "The soldier had worn armor, perhaps even better than the kind anyone in her mercenary company had, and the creature had sliced through it like it was nothing."

    old "Suddenly it rushed forward."
    new "Suddenly it rushed forward."

    old "As it reached the center of the soldiers, it turned around on itself, its tail striking out like a whip."
    new "As it reached the center of the soldiers, it turned around on itself, its tail striking out like a whip."

    old "A group of soldiers, too slow to run away, exploded into red mist as the thing's tail slashed through them."
    new "A group of soldiers, too slow to run away, exploded into red mist as the thing's tail slashed through them."

    old "There was no time to process."
    new "There was no time to process."

    old "As it spun and whipped its tail, its claws reached out, gripping, crushing anyone it caught in its range."
    new "As it spun and whipped its tail, its claws reached out, gripping, crushing anyone it caught in its range."

    old "It moved with such speed that no sooner had the soldiers turned to it, that it had already positioned itself anew."
    new "It moved with such speed that no sooner had the soldiers turned to it, that it had already positioned itself anew."

    old "Each time a group of soldiers tried to rush for the door, the creature would snap back, catching them."
    new "Each time a group of soldiers tried to rush for the door, the creature would snap back, catching them."

    old "Sarah felt the screams grow louder."
    new "Sarah felt the screams grow louder."

    old "Soldiers were running off into every direction, but the army was trapped in the room with no escape."
    new "Soldiers were running off into every direction, but the army was trapped in the room with no escape."

    old "And yet they still ran, if only so they could hope to die last."
    new "And yet they still ran, if only so they could hope to die last."

    old "Sarah watched Vaelen, knelt down, hoping to hide himself from the creature's sight."
    new "Sarah watched Vaelen, knelt down, hoping to hide himself from the creature's sight."

    old "Even he didn't have a plan for them to escape."
    new "Even he didn't have a plan for them to escape."

    old "They were all going to die."
    new "They were all going to die."

    old "Sarah knew it as surely as she had ever known anything in her life. In her mind's eye, she could see it play out again and again."
    new "Sarah knew it as surely as she had ever known anything in her life. In her mind's eye, she could see it play out again and again."

    old "Then, her heart soared."
    new "Then, her heart soared."

    old "The screams slowly faded around her. A different voice spoke. It too spoke to her with her own voice, yet she knew it to be different."
    new "The screams slowly faded around her. A different voice spoke. It too spoke to her with her own voice, yet she knew it to be different."

    old "Stay here!"
    new "Stay here!"

    old "What are you going to do?"
    new "What are you going to do?"

    old "Just stay here and no matter what, don't try to make a run for the door."
    new "Just stay here and no matter what, don't try to make a run for the door."

    old "Sarah strode out onto the center of the throne room, drawing out her blade from its sheath."
    new "Sarah strode out onto the center of the throne room, drawing out her blade from its sheath."

    old "Each step measured. Each step exactly as she knew it."
    new "Each step measured. Each step exactly as she knew it."

    old "All around her, a vast space. Most soldiers had ran for the edges of the room, hiding behind pillars or any other object that might give them shelter."
    new "All around her, a vast space. Most soldiers had ran for the edges of the room, hiding behind pillars or any other object that might give them shelter."

    old "The center was open."
    new "The center was open."

    old "Seizing her blade with both hands, Sarah raised her sword up besides herself."
    new "Seizing her blade with both hands, Sarah raised her sword up besides herself."

    old "Come!"
    new "Come!"

    old "She screamed the word, half to challenge, half to bolster her own confidence."
    new "She screamed the word, half to challenge, half to bolster her own confidence."

    old "The creature turned towards her, as if obeying her command."
    new "The creature turned towards her, as if obeying her command."

    old "She stared into its face and she could see, despite the lack of its eyes, that the thing looked back into her."
    new "She stared into its face and she could see, despite the lack of its eyes, that the thing looked back into her."

    old "The only thought that Sarah could ask herself, again and again."
    new "The only thought that Sarah could ask herself, again and again."

    old "And yet, as though her body moved to a different beat, she had ventured out to face the creature."
    new "And yet, as though her body moved to a different beat, she had ventured out to face the creature."

    old "For a moment, the thing lingered."
    new "For a moment, the thing lingered."

    old "Then, the thing's tail sprung like a coil, launching itself towards her."
    new "Then, the thing's tail sprung like a coil, launching itself towards her."

    old "By less than a heartbeat, Sarah stepped aside and felt the creature rush past her."
    new "By less than a heartbeat, Sarah stepped aside and felt the creature rush past her."

    old "She felt the tremors and heard the creature's claws digging into the earth, halting its rush and allowing it to turn back to her."
    new "She felt the tremors and heard the creature's claws digging into the earth, halting its rush and allowing it to turn back to her."

    old "Sarah spun and thrusted out her blade, catching the creature in its face."
    new "Sarah spun and thrusted out her blade, catching the creature in its face."

    old "Suddenly, the beast lunged back, surprised that anything might have hurt it."
    new "Suddenly, the beast lunged back, surprised that anything might have hurt it."

    old "Sarah could see something in the beast's movements. An uncertainty."
    new "Sarah could see something in the beast's movements. An uncertainty."

    old "The moment passed as the thing launched itself upwards, descending upon her again, now from above."
    new "The moment passed as the thing launched itself upwards, descending upon her again, now from above."

    old "Sarah rolled and swung her blade up in an arc, catching the creature by the joint of its leg."
    new "Sarah rolled and swung her blade up in an arc, catching the creature by the joint of its leg."

    old "A deafening scream erupted from the creature as it crashed into the stone floor, its limb smashing against the ground with a loud thud."
    new "A deafening scream erupted from the creature as it crashed into the stone floor, its limb smashing against the ground with a loud thud."

    old "But her body moved quicker still."
    new "But her body moved quicker still."

    old "Spinning around again, Sarah brought her blade down with a plowman's strength, hewing her sword deep into its back."
    new "Spinning around again, Sarah brought her blade down with a plowman's strength, hewing her sword deep into its back."

    old "A black liquid spewed out, covering part of her face and armor, and the beast roared again."
    new "A black liquid spewed out, covering part of her face and armor, and the beast roared again."

    old "As she pulled her blade back, she could feel the thing's flesh rip and tear."
    new "As she pulled her blade back, she could feel the thing's flesh rip and tear."

    old "Raising her sword high above her head, she brought it down again with both hands."
    new "Raising her sword high above her head, she brought it down again with both hands."

    old "Again, she could feel the beast thrash. Its scream drowned out all other senses. More blood spewed forth, pooling on the floor."
    new "Again, she could feel the beast thrash. Its scream drowned out all other senses. More blood spewed forth, pooling on the floor."

    old "Rip."
    new "Rip."

    old "Tear."
    new "Tear."

    old "Raising her sword above her head for yet another blow, Sarah caught a shade moving in the corner of her eyes."
    new "Raising her sword above her head for yet another blow, Sarah caught a shade moving in the corner of her eyes."

    old "Too late, Sarah only realized it was the creature's tail when it struck her across the head."
    new "Too late, Sarah only realized it was the creature's tail when it struck her across the head."

    old "So great was the impact of the force that Sarah felt herself topple over, her entire body spinning, rolling across the floor, the clattering of metal as her armor broke her fall."
    new "So great was the impact of the force that Sarah felt herself topple over, her entire body spinning, rolling across the floor, the clattering of metal as her armor broke her fall."

    old "Hold on, she screamed in her mind, hold onto your sword."
    new "Hold on, she screamed in her mind, hold onto your sword."

    old "When she finally stopped rolling, Sarah tried to push herself back up."
    new "When she finally stopped rolling, Sarah tried to push herself back up."

    old "No sooner did she try when she saw the creature lunge for her."
    new "No sooner did she try when she saw the creature lunge for her."

    old "She rolled to the side, again the creature missed her."
    new "She rolled to the side, again the creature missed her."

    old "She felt it reach for her with the stump of its limb."
    new "She felt it reach for her with the stump of its limb."

    old "Continuing the motion of her roll, Sarah positioned herself back onto her feet."
    new "Continuing the motion of her roll, Sarah positioned herself back onto her feet."

    old "This time, she caught the thing's tail in time."
    new "This time, she caught the thing's tail in time."

    old "Ducking low and raising her blade up, she felt it cut through the thing's tail as the beast swiped it into her blade. A loud thud of something falling behind her."
    new "Ducking low and raising her blade up, she felt it cut through the thing's tail as the beast swiped it into her blade. A loud thud of something falling behind her."

    old "Its face rushed towards her."
    new "Its face rushed towards her."

    old "The thing's razor sharp teeth, a mouth opening and shutting with a sickening chomp."
    new "The thing's razor sharp teeth, a mouth opening and shutting with a sickening chomp."

    old "She stepped back, sweeping her blade across as she kept stepping backwards, she caught the creature across its face, holding it off, injuring it each time it tried to snap her in its jaws."
    new "She stepped back, sweeping her blade across as she kept stepping backwards, she caught the creature across its face, holding it off, injuring it each time it tried to snap her in its jaws."

    old "A fury was building in the thing, she could hear its screams mix with an animalistic fury, something close to a hiss."
    new "A fury was building in the thing, she could hear its screams mix with an animalistic fury, something close to a hiss."

    old "As it began to wildly swipe its claws at her, Sarah dove in under it, thrusting her blade up, she caught another of the creature's limbs."
    new "As it began to wildly swipe its claws at her, Sarah dove in under it, thrusting her blade up, she caught another of the creature's limbs."

    old "For a moment, her blade remained buried in the beast's flesh, but with a titan's effort, Sarah pulled out the blade, cutting away what little remained of the creature's limb."
    new "For a moment, her blade remained buried in the beast's flesh, but with a titan's effort, Sarah pulled out the blade, cutting away what little remained of the creature's limb."

    old "Leaping back, Sarah looked upon the thing."
    new "Leaping back, Sarah looked upon the thing."

    old "Deprived of two of its limbs, the thing stumbled upon itself, its inky belly slithering across the floor, leaving a pool of black blood as it tried to approach her."
    new "Deprived of two of its limbs, the thing stumbled upon itself, its inky belly slithering across the floor, leaving a pool of black blood as it tried to approach her."

    old "It's hissing had grown deeper, more exhausted, its attacks slower."
    new "It's hissing had grown deeper, more exhausted, its attacks slower."

    old "As it lunged for her again, Sarah was ready, bringing her blade down across its face, splitting the thing's mask apart."
    new "As it lunged for her again, Sarah was ready, bringing her blade down across its face, splitting the thing's mask apart."

    old "It screamed more loudly than it ever had before."
    new "It screamed more loudly than it ever had before."

    old "All of its body flinched and writhed around the room, thrasing violently as it sought to deal with the pain."
    new "All of its body flinched and writhed around the room, thrasing violently as it sought to deal with the pain."

    old "But with each wild movement, its body slowed."
    new "But with each wild movement, its body slowed."

    old "With each scream, its voice dimmed."
    new "With each scream, its voice dimmed."

    old "Slowly, the thing began to drag, and eventually, ceased to move altogther."
    new "Slowly, the thing began to drag, and eventually, ceased to move altogther."

    old "Sarah walked around the thing, carefuly."
    new "Sarah walked around the thing, carefuly."

    old "She saw the thing's body rise and fall, its breathing laboured."
    new "She saw the thing's body rise and fall, its breathing laboured."

    old "As she moved in closer, the creature swiped for her with its claws, but by now it was so slow that it had no chance to catch her."
    new "As she moved in closer, the creature swiped for her with its claws, but by now it was so slow that it had no chance to catch her."

    old "Stepping back, Sarah dodged the beast's hopeless attack, and again moved in closer."
    new "Stepping back, Sarah dodged the beast's hopeless attack, and again moved in closer."

    old "Leaping forward, Sarah drove her blade deep into the creature's belly."
    new "Leaping forward, Sarah drove her blade deep into the creature's belly."

    old "More of its black innards and blood spewed out across the floor, but now the creature was too weak to even cry out. It only grunted in deep pain."
    new "More of its black innards and blood spewed out across the floor, but now the creature was too weak to even cry out. It only grunted in deep pain."

    old "Sarah pulled her blade out, raised it over her head, and with the force of both hands hewed it into the creature."
    new "Sarah pulled her blade out, raised it over her head, and with the force of both hands hewed it into the creature."

    old "Rip. Tear. Pull."
    new "Rip. Tear. Pull."

    old "Sarah felt her face, her hair, her armor, covered in the creature's ichor."
    new "Sarah felt her face, her hair, her armor, covered in the creature's ichor."

    old "So drenched in the thing's blood, Sarah could feel even her grip on her sword's handle slip."
    new "So drenched in the thing's blood, Sarah could feel even her grip on her sword's handle slip."

    old "But she committed herself to her butcher's work with a zeal, strengthened her grip, and hewed the blade down again."
    new "But she committed herself to her butcher's work with a zeal, strengthened her grip, and hewed the blade down again."

    old "She had ceased to count, but somewhere in the slaughter, she finally regained her senses."
    new "She had ceased to count, but somewhere in the slaughter, she finally regained her senses."

    old "Her blade remained buried in the body of the beast, but it no longer moved. It no longer made a sound."
    new "Her blade remained buried in the body of the beast, but it no longer moved. It no longer made a sound."

    old "Staring down at her hands, Sarah could hardly make out her once shining armor, now stained black."
    new "Staring down at her hands, Sarah could hardly make out her once shining armor, now stained black."

    old "She felt her hair, sticking to her neck as she turned to look up."
    new "She felt her hair, sticking to her neck as she turned to look up."

    old "All around her, she saw the hestitant faces of the soldiers, emerging from behind their hiding places."
    new "All around her, she saw the hestitant faces of the soldiers, emerging from behind their hiding places."

    old "Even they could barely believe she had ended the thing."
    new "Even they could barely believe she had ended the thing."

    old "Pulling out the blade and rending the thing's flesh one final time, Sarah raised up her sword and screamed."
